HEADWORD: Overlash
<hw>O`ver*lash"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Prov. E.
<ets>lash</ets> extravagant, <ets>lashing</ets> lavish.]</ety> <def>To
drive on rashly; to go to excess; hence, to exaggerate; to boast.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Barrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

